text: A chaotic first debate and President Trump’s Covid-19 diagnosis set the stage for the #VPDebate. Follow our live coverage and analysis. https://t.co/fmJsTeEgAb

name: WSJ
text: RT @benpershing: “It’s like Covid-19 theater,” one scientist says. The plexiglass barriers installed at the vice-presidential debate to reduce the risk of spreading the coronavirus probably won’t help, according to experts. https://t.co/qAa6ulWCTe

name: WSJ
text: Kamala Harris called President Trump’s response to the coronavirus “the greatest failure of any presidential administration in the history of our country" at the #VPDebate, while Mike Pence said Joe Biden’s plan for the virus looks like "plagiarism" https://t.co/vFn8UJGvHm

name: WSJ
text: RT @WSJPolitics: Vice President Pence said he and the president trust people to make wise choices about their health and accused Kamala Harris and Joe Biden of wanting to put mandates on everything from coronavirus response to health care in general. https://t.co/woYCqlZNzC #VPDebate

name: WSJ
text: In a discussion at the #VPDebate about financial transparency and President Trump's refusal to release his tax returns, Sen. Kamala Harris said "the American people have a right to know what is influencing the president's decisions" https://t.co/DHiuayEgF2

name: WSJ
text: Neither Mike Pence nor Kamala Harris would say at the #VPDebate whether they've had a conversation with their running mates about potentially taking over the world's most powerful job https://t.co/VLT5KSWXLK

text: RT @willmauldin: Pence says Biden is a "cheerleader for communist China" but Harris faults Trump's tariffs on Chinese imports followed by a phase one trade deal: "You lost that trade war with China," she says. https://t.co/NvgyRVNqu2 #VPdebate
